  "prompt": "How does the legal system address complex money laundering schemes?",
  "response": "The legal system addresses money laundering through various mechanisms:\n\n1. Anti-Money Laundering (AML) Laws\n- Comprehensive regulations\n- Reporting requirements for financial institutions\n- Mandatory suspicious transaction monitoring\n\n2. Investigation Techniques\n- Financial forensic analysis\n- Tracing money flows\n- Collaboration between law enforcement agencies\n\n3. Prosecution Strategies\n- Criminal charges\n- Asset seizure\n- International cooperation\n- Targeting both money launderers and facilitators\n\n4. International Frameworks\n- FATF (Financial Action Task Force) guidelines\n- Cross-border information sharing\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n\n5. Technology and Compliance\n- Advanced transaction monitoring systems\n- Risk-based compliance approaches\n- Enhanced due diligence protocols\n\nThese approaches aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute complex money laundering activities.",
